        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria — Gradation 3 mesh convergence",
        "description": "Richardson extrapolation applied to three mesh densities (coarse ~80k elements, medium ~240k, fine ~720k). Grid Convergence Index (GCI) for stiffness QoI must be < 2% and for yield force < 3%. Monotonic convergence must be demonstrated."
      },
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm construct. GCI for construct stiffness was 1.4% (fine-to-medium) and for yield force was 2.1%, both within acceptance bounds. Monotonic convergence confirmed with observed order of accuracy p=1.92, consistent with second-order elements. Production mesh uses the medium density (~240k elements) balancing accuracy and computational cost."
