        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — Gradation 3 physics justification",
        "description": "Constitutive model selection (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V, linear elastic for UHMWPE blocks) justified by published material characterisation data. Contact formulation (augmented Lagrangian, friction coefficient 0.2 ± 0.05) justified by tribological literature for dry titanium-on-titanium contact."
      },
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V pedicle screw and rod material behaviour is represented by a bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated to ASTM E8 tensile coupon data (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.8 GPa) consistent with published literature (Donachie 2000). UHMWPE test blocks treated as linear elastic (E=1.0 GPa, ν=0.46) per ASTM F648. Augmented Lagrangian contact with μ=0.2 is consistent with published dry titanium contact tribology. Model form assessed at Gradation 3."
