      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/ac/nagaraja-cou1-val-activity-relevance-ac",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria — Gradation 3 high fidelity COU match",
        "description": "Validation activity must use production-representative implant geometry, production-lot materials, and the identical test protocol (ASTM F1717) as the COU. Any simplification relative to the COU must be documented and shown to be conservative or negligible in influence."
      },
      "rationale": "The validation activity uses production-lot non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws and rods assembled per surgical technique guide, tested under the identical ASTM F1717 protocol specified in the COU. No geometric simplifications were introduced relative to the COU. The only acknowledged difference is that validation was performed at ambient temperature (23°C) while in-vivo conditions involve body temperature (37°C); the influence of this 14°C difference on Ti-6Al-4V mechanical properties is < 1% per published data (Boyer et al. 1994) and is documented in the sensitivity analysis. Gradation 3 satisfied."
    }
